## Introduction

The Claw Command Officer (later CCO) is a specialized member of the Blueshield program tasked with protecting Command and Crew onboard the station. Alongside advising its crew and command in regard to SOP and safety.

## Their Place in the Chain of Command

The CCO answers directly to Central Command; however, they are obliged to follow any reasonable orders from NTR, Captain, Head of Personnel, and Head of Security. It is also advised (not required) they follow any reasonable requests from department heads and, optionally, crew. Their requests are to be prioritized in accordance with the chain of command, with NTR having priority.

## Promoting and Demoting a CCO

CCO answers directly to Central Command; however, they may be demoted if a vote including all present departmental heads (including NTR) is held and at least 75% of votes are supporting the decision. Votes of the captain and NTR count as 2. Central Command is to be informed via fax if such a vote is held, even if it does not result in a demotion. In situations of emergency, the captain, with the approval of the NTR, if one is present, may hold such a vote via radio communication methods.

The crew is forbidden from electing an acting CCO without Central Command approval. However, if one is granted for a candidate, they must be additionally approved by 75% of votes (Captains and NTRs vote count as 2) during an in-person vote.

## CCO's responsibilities and requirements:

- CCO is permitted to carry lethal munition and longarms at all times; however, longarms cannot be chambered with lethal munition on Green alert.

- CCO is to prioritize safety of Command members in accordance with the Chain of Command, with priority given to NTR.

- CCO is allowed to perform arrests if no Command member is in danger; however, they must follow security SOP when doing so.

- CCO is permitted to use lethal force when defending self, a command member, or crew from clear and present danger; however, is advised to warn the attacker of it if the situation enables it.

